Cloaked in illusion, the target becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Invisible]{Invisible}. This makes it @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Undetected]{Undetected} to all creatures, though the creatures can attempt to find the target, making it @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Hidden]{Hidden} to them instead. If the target uses a hostile action, the spell ends after that hostile action is completed.

Heightened (4th) The spell lasts 1 minute, but it doesn't end if the target uses a hostile action.

Bolstered by magical power, the target grows to size Large. Its equipment grows with it but returns to natural size if removed. The creature is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1}. Its reach increases by 5 feet (or by 10 feet if it started out Tiny), and it gains a +2 status bonus to melee damage. This spell has no effect on a Large or larger creature.

@Compendium[pf2e.spell-effects.Spell Effect: Enlarge]{Spell Effect: Enlarge}

Heightened (4th) The creature instead grows to size Huge. The status bonus to melee damage is +4 and the creature's reach increases by 10 feet (or 15 feet if the creature started out Tiny). The spell has no effect on a Huge or larger creature. @Compendium[pf2e.spell-effects.Spell Effect: Enlarge (Heightened 4th)]{Spell Effect: Enlarge (Heightened 4th)}

Heightened (6th) Choose either the 2nd-level or 4th-level version of this spell and apply its effects to 10 willing creatures.

Activate A Strike

This flask filled with corrosive acid deals 1 acid damage, 3d6 persistent acid damage, and 3 acid splash damage. You gain a +2 item bonus to attack rolls.

Activate A Strike

Alchemist's fire is a combination of volatile liquids that ignite when exposed to air. Alchemist's fire deals 3d8 fire damage, 3 persistent fire damage, and 3 fire splash damage. You gain a +2 item bonus to attack rolls.

You need an alchemist's lab to Craft alchemical items during downtime.

An expanded alchemist's lab gives a +1 item bonus to Crafting checks to create alchemical items.

Automatically applied effects:

  • +1 item bonus to Crafting alchemical item

This silver signet ring changes to match the insignia of a lord or organization you serve (or your own face, if you serve no one else). It grants you a +3 item bonus to Diplomacy checks and lets you cast @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Message]{Message} as an arcane innate spell at will.

Activate 1 minute (envision)

Frequency once per day

Effect The ring casts @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Animal Messenger]{Animal Messenger} to your specification. The animal is a magical creature that springs from the ring, and its appearance suits the iconography or heraldry of the lord or organization represented by the ring.

Activate T command

Frequency once per hour

Effect The ring casts @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Sending]{Sending} to your specifications.

Automatically applied effects:

  • +3 item bonus to Diplomacy checks

This bitter draught opens your mind to the potential of the written word. For the listed duration after drinking this elixir, you can understand any words you read, so long as they are written in a common language. This elixir doesn't automatically allow you to understand codes or extremely esoteric passages-you still need to attempt a skill check to Decipher Writing. The duration is 10 minutes.

Activate A Interact

An antidote protects you against toxins. Upon drinking an antidote, you gain a +4 item bonus to Fortitude saving throws against poisons for 6 hours, and when you drink the antidote, you can immediately attempt a saving throw against one poison of 14th level or lower affecting you. If you succeed, the poison is neutralized.

@Compendium[pf2e.consumable-effects.Effect: Antidote (Major)]{Effect: Antidote (Major)}

Activate A Interact

Elixirs of life accelerate a living creature''s natural healing processes and immune system. Upon drinking this elixir, you regain [[/r 7d6+18]] Hit Points and gain +2 item bonus to saving throws against diseases and poisons for 10 minutes.

@Compendium[pf2e.consumable-effects.Effect: Elixir of Life (Greater)]{Effect: Elixir of Life (Greater)}
7 acid damage plus 3d6 persistent acid damage and 9 acid splash damage
plus 3 persistent fire and 9 fire splash

A monster with darkvision can see perfectly well in areas of darkness and dim light, though such vision is in black and white only. Some forms of magical darkness, such as a 4th-level @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Darkness]{Darkness} spell, block normal darkvision. A monster with @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.Greater Darkvision]{Greater Darkvision}, however, can see through even these forms of magical darkness.

When first exposed to bright light, the monster is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} until the end of its next turn. After this exposure, light doesn't blind the monster again until after it spends 1 hour in darkness. However, as long as the monster is in an area of bright light, it's @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Dazzled]{Dazzled}.

Qormintur reminds others of the punishments Shraens mete out for failure. Qormintur and all allies within 60 feet of her gain a +1 status bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls until the end of Qormintur’s next turn.
Qormintur Interacts to draw an alchemical bomb, then Strikes with it.

Requirements: Qormintur is wielding a piercing or slashing weapon and has a free hand;

Cost: 1 batch of infused reagents;

Effect: Qormintur applies reagents to the weapon. The weapon deals an additional 2d10 poison damage for 1 minute.

Qormintur automatically disbelieves all illusions

of 8th level or lower.

When Qormintur rolls a success on a Fortitude

save, she gets a critical success instead.
Qormintur's bombs deal splash damage to every creature within 10 feet of the target.

When throwing an alchemical bomb with the

splash trait, Qormintur can choose to deal splash

damage to her primary target only, rather than

dealing the usual splash damage.

Qormintur’s range increment for bombs

is 60 feet. She reduces any circumstance bonus to the

target’s AC from cover by 1, and she automatically

succeeds at the flat check when she targets a

concealed creature.

Your body is accustomed to physical hardship and resistant to ailments. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Fortitude save, you get a critical success instead.
